Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
setIlmMode(25.10)                                            setIlmMode(25.10)

Name
       setIlmMode - Controls certain behaviors of ILM commands

Syntax
       setIlmMode

       [-help]

       [-reset]

       [-filterInternalPath {true|false}]

       [-keepAsync {true|false}]

       [-keepHighFanoutPorts {true|false}]

       [-keepInstInSdc {true|false}]

       [-ilm <ilmName>]

       [-ilmCell <ilmCellName>]

       [-keepFlatten {true|false}]

       [-keepLoopBack {true|false}]

       [-map {view|corner}]

       [-maxNumInsts <maxInstances>]

       [-maxNumRegisters <maxRegisters>]

       [-resetMap {view|corner}]

       [-slackDriven {true|false}]

       [-top <topViewName>]

       Controls certain behaviors of ILM commands.

       Use  the  getIlmMode  command  to  display the current settings for the
       setIlmMode command.

       You can set certain options through setIlmMode which  can  control  how
       ILMs are created or the way top level is mapped to ILMs in case of mis-
       match between view/corner naming between block and top.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each setIlmMode parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man setIlmMode.

       -filterInternalPath {true|false}
              Filters the internal path kept by ILM. When set to  true,  group
              paths  are  created  for internal paths with slack adjustment of
              9999. Therefore, all internal paths are filtered  out  from  the
              timing report.

              Default: false

       -keepAsync {true | false}
              Keeps  paths from asynchronous input ports when ILMs are created
              by createInterfaceLogic. For example, paths from an  input  port
              to  the  reset pin of interface sequential instances, but not to
              the internal sequential instances.

              Default: false

       -keepHighFanoutPorts {true | false}
              Keeps high-fanin outputs and high-fanout inputs  when  ILMs  are
              created by createInterfaceLogic.

              Default: true

       -keepInstInSdc {true|false}
              Keeps instances which have constraints on it.

              Default: false

       <-ilm ilmViewName>|<ilmCornerName>
              Specifies the view or corner name of an ILM that is to be mapped
              to the top level.

       -ilmCell <ilmCellName>
              Specifies  the  cell name of an ILM that has view or corner map-
              ping to the top level.

       -keepFlatten {true|false}
              Makes flow work under the flattenIlm mode.

              Default: true

       -keepLoopBack {true | false}
              Keeps loop back paths when ILMs are created by createInterfaceL-
              ogic.

              When set to true, then any path touching a net used for the  ILM
              model  is also included. This is done for better model accuracy,
              so that the actual capacitance on an output  port  could  affect
              the delay on a net which feeds an internal path that is normally
              not  included in the ILM model. This also degrades the reduction
              ratio (#ILM_insts/#all_inst) for the block.

              Default: false

       -map {view | corner}
              Maps a view or corner specified in an ILM to a view or corner of
              the top-design analysis.

              Default: view

       -maxNumInsts <maxInstances>
              Specifies the maximum number of instances.

              Default:1000

       -maxNumRegisters <maxRegisters>
              Specifies the maximum number of registers per port to be consid-
              ered as high fanout ports.  This  setting  will  be  honored  by
              -keepHighFanoutPorts.

              Default: 40

       -reset Resets all or specified options to default value.

              Any  values  that do not already match the default value and are
              reset will be reported.

       -resetMap {view | corner}
              Resets view or corner mapping between an ILM and the top level.

              Default: view

       -slackDriven {true|false}
              Specifies slack driven ILM generation.

              Default: false

       -top <topViewName>|<topCornerName>
              Specifies the view or corner name of top design  analysis  while
              creating the mapping between the ILM and the top level.

              Default: ""

       Loop-Back Paths

Examples
              * The  following  command  does  not keep high fanout ports when
                ILMs are created by createInterfaceLogic:

                setIlmMode -keepHighFanoutPorts false

              * The following command resets the -keepHighFanoutPorts  parame-
                ter to its original value:

                setIlmMode -reset -keepHighFanoutPorts

              * The  following  command  undoes  all  the view mapping for ILM
                modA:

                setIlmMode -resetMap view -ilmCell modA

              * The following command maps the view of maxCnr_setup of the ILM
                blkA to the top design analysis view of rcMAX_setup:

                setIlmMode -map view -top rcMAX_setup -ilmCell blkA -ilm  max-
                Cnr_setup

              * The  following  command  undoes all the corner mapping for ILM
                blkA:

                setIlmMode -resetMap corner -ilmCell blkA

Related Information
